{#- §04 PLANS (Core/Premium/Elite → pricing-style .ptier cards; featured = note) — white -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="payroll-plans">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">The plans</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="max-width:22ch;margin-bottom:10px;">QuickBooks Payroll plans, without the sales pitch.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 36px;max-width:60ch;">Plan names and inclusions reflect Intuit&rsquo;s QuickBooks Online Payroll structure; Intuit sets and may change features and pricing. A ProAdvisor confirms the current structure during the discovery call.</p>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for p in plans %}
      <article class="ptier{% if p.note %} ptier--featured{% endif %}">
        {%- if p.note %}<p class="ptier__flag">{{ p.note | safe }}</p>{%- endif %}
        <h3 class="ptier__name">{{ p.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="ptier__for">{{ p.price | safe }}</p>
        <ul>
          {%- for b in p.bullets %}<li>{{ b | safe }}</li>{%- endfor %}
        </ul>
      </article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <div class="prose" style="margin-top:32px;max-width:70ch;">
      <p>Still on QuickBooks Desktop? Desktop Payroll remains available, but Intuit is steering most customers toward Online Payroll and Desktop is on a sunset timeline. If you&rsquo;re evaluating payroll while still on Desktop, it&rsquo;s usually worth scoping a <a href="/quickbooks/migration/?intent=quickbooks-migration">migration</a> at the same time &mdash; doing both together avoids configuring payroll twice.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- §05 WAYS (four engagements → numbered .lift cards with fee/eng + link) — sand -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="payroll-ways" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">How a ProAdvisor helps</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="max-width:22ch;margin-bottom:36px;">Four ways a Payroll ProAdvisor helps.</h2>
    <div class="r-2">
      {%- for w in ways %}
      <div class="lift">
        <span class="lift__n">{% if loop.index < 10 %}0{% endif %}{{ loop.index }}</span>
        <div>
          <h3>{{ w.name | safe }}</h3>
          <p>{{ w.body | safe }}</p>
          <p style="margin-top:8px;"><strong>{{ w.fee | safe }}</strong> &middot; {{ w.eng | safe }}</p>
          <p style="margin-top:8px;"><a href="{{ w.href }}" style="color:var(--color-accent);font-weight:600;font-size:14px;">{{ w.name | safe }} <span class="lnk-arrow" aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span></a></p>
        </div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- §06 MULTI-STATE & LOCAL TAX (honest prose + .opquote pull-quote) — white -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="payroll-multistate">
  <div class="ct read">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Where it goes wrong</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="max-width:24ch;margin-bottom:18px;">Multi-state &amp; local tax: the part QuickBooks Payroll won&rsquo;t fix for you.</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>QuickBooks Payroll automates filing &mdash; but only based on how it&rsquo;s configured. The software files exactly what you tell it to, which means a configuration error becomes a filing error becomes a state notice. The failures cluster in predictable places: work state vs. residence state, reciprocity agreements between neighboring states, and &mdash; the deepest trap &mdash; local jurisdiction tax. Indiana has county income tax (CAGIT/COIT) tied to the employee&rsquo;s January-1 county of residence; Ohio has municipal tax through RITA and CCA; Pennsylvania has local earned-income tax keyed to PSD codes; New York City and Yonkers have resident taxes. QuickBooks supports all of these &mdash; but only if a human configures them correctly, and they&rsquo;re the single most common thing left unconfigured.</p>
    </div>
    <blockquote class="opquote" style="margin-top:28px;"><blockquote>{{ multistate.body | safe }}</blockquote></blockquote>
  </div>
</section>

